ce in the North Caucasus\n|publisher=Routledge\n|isbn=978-0765620286\n}}\n\n* {{Citation\n| last1       = Akhmadov\n| first1      = Ilyas\n| authorlink1 = Ilyas Akhmadov\n| last2       = Lanskoy\n| first2      = Miriam\n| authorlink2 = Miriam Lanskoy\n| last3       = Brzezinski\n| first3      = Zbigniew\n| authorlink3 = Zbigniew Brzezinski\n| title       = The Chechen Struggle: Independence Won and Lost\n| year        = 2010\n| publisher   = Palgrave Macmillan\n| isbn        = 978-0-230-10534-8\n}}\n\n* {{Citation\n| last1       = Soldatov\n| first1      = Andrei\n| authorlink1 = Andrei Soldatov\n| last2       = Borogan\n| first2      = Irina\n| authorlink2 = Irina Borogan\n| title       = The New Nobility: The Restoration of Russia's Security State and the Enduring Legacy of the KGB\n| year        = 2010\n| publisher   = PublicAffairs\n| isbn        = 978-1-58648-802-4\n}}\n\n* {{Citation\n| first      = John\n| last       = Dunlop\n| authorlink = John B. Dunlop\n| title      = The Moscow Bombings of September 1999: Examinations of Russian Terrorist Attacks at the Onset of Vladimir Putin's Rule\n| publisher  = Stuttgart: Ibidem\n| year       = 2012\n| isbn       = 978-3-8382-0388-1\n}}\n\n* {{Citation\n| first      = Brian Glyn\n| last       = Williams\n| authorlink = Brian Glyn Williams\n| title      = Inferno in Chechnya: The Russian-Chechen Wars, the Al Qaeda Myth, and the Boston Marathon Bombings\n| publisher  = ForeEdge\n| year       = 2015\n| isbn       = 978-1-61168-737-8\n}}\n\n* {{Citation\n| first      = Elena\n| last       = Pokalova\n| title      = Chechnya's Terrorist Network: The Evolution of Terrorism in Russia's North Caucasus\n| publisher  = [[Greenwood Publishing Group|Praeger]]\n| year       = 2015\n| isbn       = 978-1-44083-154-6\n}}\n\n{{Chechen wars}}\n[[Category:Explosions in 1999]]\n[[Category:Russian apartment bombings| ]]\n[[Category:Censorship in Russia]]\n[[Category:Deep politics]]\n[[Category:Vladimir Putin]]\n[[Category:Building collapses in Russia]]\n[[Category:Chechen\u2013Russian conflict]]\n[[Category:Events in Moscow]]\n[[Category:Terrorist incidents in Russia in 1999]]\n[[Category:Improvised explosive device bombings in Russia]]\n[[Category:Mass murder in 1999]]\n[[Category:20th-century mass murder in Russia]]\n[[Category:Conflicts in 1999]]\n[[Category:Massacres in Russia]]\n[[Category:1999 crimes in Russia]]\n[[Category:Murder in Moscow]]\n[[Category:Federal Security Service of the Russian Federation]]\n[[Category:Second Chechen War]]\n[[Category:Terrorist incidents in Moscow]]\n[[Category:1999 in Moscow]]\n[[Category:September 1999 events in Europe]]\n", "name_user": "Document hippo", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eFiction:more close to the text", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Russian_apartment_bombings"}
{"title_page": "The Untamed (TV series)", "text_new": "{{Infobox television\n| show_name                = The Untamed\n| image                    = Theuntamed.jpg\n| caption                  = \n| show_name_2              = \n| genre                    = [[Xianxia novel|Xianxia]]\n| based_on                 = ''[[Mo Dao Zu Shi]]'' by Mo Xiang Tong Xiu\n| writer                   = Yang Xia<br>Deng Yaoyu<br>Ma Jing<br>Guo Guangyun\n| director                 = Zheng Weiwen<br>Chen Jialin\n| starring                 = [[Xiao Zhan]]<br>[[Wang Yibo]]\n| voices                   = \n| opentheme                = \n| endtheme                 = \"Unrestrained\" by [[Xiao Zhan]] & [[Wang Yibo]]\n| composer                 = Lin Hai\n| country                  = China\n| language                 = Mandarin\n| num_seasons              = 1\n| num_episodes             = 50\n| list_episodes            = List of The Untamed episodes\n| executive_producer       = Sun Huaizhong<br>Wang Xin<br><br>Han Zhijie\n| producer                 = Fang Fang<br>Yang Xia<br>Zhang Meng<br>Wang Chu<br>Ren Qiang<br>Liu Mingtie<br>Wang Wanning\n| location                 = [[Hengdian World Studios]]<br>[[Guizhou]]\n| cinematography           = \n| editor                   = \n| runtime                  = 45 minutes per episode\n| company                  = [[Tencent Pictures|Tencent Penguin Pictures]]<br>New Style Media\n| channel                  = [[Tencent Video]]\n| picture_format           = [[1080i]] ([[HDTV]])\n| audio_format             = \n| first_run                = \n| first_aired              = {{Start date|2019|6|27}}\n| last_aired               = {{End date|2019|8|20}}\n| preceded_by              = \n| followed_by              = \n| related                  = ''[[Mo Dao Zu Shi]]''\n| website                  = https://www.weibo.com/u/5921252454\n| website_title            = \n| production_website       = \n| production_website_title = \n| camera                   = [[Multiple-camera setup|Multi-camera]]\n}}\n'''''The Untamed ''''' ({{zh|c= \u9648\u60c5\u4ee4|p=Ch\u00e9n Q\u00edng L\u00ecng}}) is a 2019 Chinese [[television series]] based on the [[Yaoi#Sh\u014dnen-ai|BL]] [[xianxia novel]] ''[[Mo Dao Zu Shi#Novel|Mo Dao Zu Shi]]'' by Mo Xiang Tong Xiu, starring [[Xiao Zhan]] and [[Wang Yibo]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ent.ifeng.com/a/20180705/43064593_0.shtml|title=\u300a\u9648\u60c5\u4ee4\u300b\u9996\u66dd\u5267\u7167 \u8096\u6218\u738b\u4e00\u535a\u6380\u4ed9\u4fa0\u98ce\u4e91|date=July 5, 2018|website=ifeng|language=zh|access-date=April 23, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180902015108/http://ent.ifeng.com/a/20180705/43064593_0.shtml|archive-date=September 2, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> The series follows the adventures of two soulmate cultivators who travel to solve a series of murder mysteries, eventually finding and defeating the true culprit.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bjnews.com.cn/ent/2019/06/27/596187.html|title=\u5f00\u64ad\u5f53\u65e5\u5b9a\u6863\uff01\u8096\u6218\u738b\u4e00\u535a\u300a\u9648\u60c5\u4ee4\u300b\u4eca\u665a\u64ad\u51fa|date=June 27, 2019|website=Beijing News|language=zh|access-date=November 10, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190718220755/http://www.bjnews.com.cn/ent/2019/06/27/596187.html|archive-date=July 18, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> It aired in China on [[Tencent Video]] from June 27 to August 20, 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://slide.ent.sina.com.cn/tv/slide_4_704_316378.html#p=1|title=\u300a\u9648\u60c5\u4ee4\u300b\u5b9a\u6863627 \u8096\u6218\u738b\u4e00\u535a\u6700\u65b0\u6d77\u62a5\u66dd\u5149|date=June 27, 2019|website=Sina|language=zh|access-date=June 27, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190629053857/http://slide.ent.sina.com.cn/tv/slide_4_704_316378.html#p=1|archive-date=June 29, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://ent.ifeng.com/a/20190814/43355188_0.shtml?_zbs_baidu_bk|title=\u300a\u9648\u60c5\u4ee4\u300b\u8fce\u5927\u7ed3\u5c40 \u8096\u6218\u738b\u4e00\u535a\u53cc\u53cc\u53d1\u6587\u544a\u522b|date=August 14, 2019|website=ifeng|language=zh|access-date=August 16, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190816192050/http://ent.ifeng.com/a/20190814/43355188_0.shtml%3F_zbs_baidu_bk|archive-date=August 16, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> A 20-episode special edition of the drama aired on WeTV starting December 25, 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://new.qq.com/omn/20191228/20191228A0MOAR00.html|title=\u300a\u9648\u60c5\u4ee4\u300b\u7279\u522b\u526a\u8f91\u7248\u4e0a\u7ebf|date=December 28, 2019|website=Tencent|language=zh}}</ref>\n\n== Synopsis ==\nThe ''[[Wuxia#Jianghu|jianghu]]'' world is ruled by the powerful Wen sect, which dominates over the smaller Lan, Jiang, Nie and Jin sects. The carefree Wei Wuxian becomes fast friends with the righteous Lan Wangji, and during their adventures, the pair find out that the head of the Wen sect is the evil mastermind behind a series of plots that would wreak havoc upon the lands.\n\nWei Wuxian's attempts to protect the innocent members of the Wen sect from unfair persecution lead to disaster, and he goes missing in the process. Wei Wuxian reappears sixteen years later, and works together with Lan Wangji to solve a series of murder mysteries, eventually finding and defeating the true culprit.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://dsj.nrta.gov.cn/tims/site/views/applications/note/noteTable.shanty?id=015f71a3efb228234028e4a05e503e86|title=\u7535\u89c6\u5267\u62cd\u6444\u5236\u4f5c\u5907\u6848\u516c\u793a\u8868 \u8bb8\u53ef\u8bc1\u53f7\uff1a 00090|website=SARFT|language=zh|accessdate=2019-12-16|date=February 2018}}</ref>\n\n== Episodes ==\n{{Main|List of The Untamed episodes}}The series aired every Thursday and Friday (GMT +08:00) with two episodes each, and VIP members could have early access to two more. On the first day of its release, a total of six episodes were available to VIP members. On June 30, 2019, their official [[Sina Weibo|Weibo]] released a new schedule<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://m.weibo.cn/status/4388821300488236?|title=\u9648\u60c5\u4ee4\u5b98\u5fae|website=Weibo|access-date=2019-06-30|language=zh}}</ref> and shifted the release from Monday to Wednesday. The series ended on August 20, 2019 with the 50th episode. On July 29, 2019 during an official fanmeeting event, they announced that VIP members would be able to watch all the episodes on August 7.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://weibo.com/5921252454/HFJPl9Uju|title=\u9648\u60c5\u4ee4\u5b98\u5fae|website=Weibo|access-date=2019-08-08|language=zh|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190808141700/https://www.weibo.com/5921252454/HFJPl9Uju|archive-date=2019-08-08|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n== Cast ==\n===Main=== \n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! style=\"width:13%\"|Actor !! style=\"width:21%\"|Character !! Introduction  \n|-\n| rowspan=2|[[Xiao Zhan]]<br> <small>Su Yaxin (young)</small> || Wei Wuxian<br>([[Chinese language|Chinese]]: \u9b4f\u65e0\u7fa1) ||Birth name: Wei Ying ([[Chinese language|Chinese]]: \u9b4f\u5a74)\nAlso known as the ''Yiling Patriarch'' ([[Chinese language|Chinese]]: \u5937\u9675\u8001\u7956), he is a Jiang sect disciple who later chooses to pursue demonic cultivation. He wields the ''Suibian'' sword ([[Chinese language|Chinese]]: \u968f\u4fbf) and ''Chenqing'' flute ([[Chinese language|Chinese]]: \u9648\u60c5), and is known for his ability to invent new spiritual techniques and inventions such as the  ''Stygian Tiger Seal'' ([[Chinese language|Chinese]]: \u9634\u864e\u7b26). He is kind-hearted, optimistic, mischievous, and loyal, and cares deeply for his friends and family. He and Lan Wangji regard each other as soulmates.\n|-\n| Mo Xuanyu <br>([[Chinese language|Chinese]]: \u83ab\u7384\u7fbd)|| The illegitimate son of Jin Guangshan and ex-disciple of the Jin sect. He sacrificed his body to Wei Wuxian through a ritual in order to fulfill his revenge plans, fueling the plot. \n|- \n| [[Wang Yibo]]<br> <small>Chen Junkai (young)</small> || Lan Wangji <br>([[Chinese language|Chinese]]: \u84dd\u5fd8\u673a)||Birth name: Lan Zhan ([[Chinese language|Chinese]]: \u84dd\u6e5b).\nAlso known as ''Lord Hanguang'' ([[Chinese language|Chinese]]: \u542b\u5149\u541b), or the ''Light Bearing Lord'',<ref name=\"viki\">{{cite web|url=https://www.viki.com/tv/36657c-the-untamed|title=The Untamed|publisher=[[Viki (website)|Viki.com]]|accessdate=2019-12-16}}</ref> he is the second young master of Lan sect and one of the Twin Jades of Lan.  He wields the ''Bichen'' sword ([[Chinese language|Chinese]]: \u907f\u5c18) and the ''Wangji'' [[Guqin|guqin]] ([[Chinese language|Chinese]]: \u5fd8\u673a). He is cold, strict, distant, and difficult to get along with, but has a good heart and a sense of justice. He holds a soft spot for Wei Wuxian, who he regards as his soulmate.\n|}\n\n===Supporting===\n\n====Gusu Lan Sect====\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! style=\"width:13%\"|Actor !! style=\"width:17%\"|Character !! Introduction  \n|-\n| Liu Haikuan<ref>{{cite web|url=http://fashion.ifeng.com/a/20180911/40411738_0.shtml|title=\u5218\u6d77\u5bbd\u6c14\u8d28\u9082\u9005ELLE30\u5468\u5e74\u76db\u5178 \u7206\u6599\u4e3a\u300a\u9648\u60c5\u4ee4\u300b\u7626\u8eab20\u65a4|date=September 11, 2018|website=ifeng|language=zh|access-date=May 3, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190503144506/http://fashion.ifeng.com/a/20180911/40411738_0.shtml|archive-date=May 3, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><br> <small>Shen Yifeng (young)</small> || Lan Xichen <br>([[Chinese language|Chinese]]:  \u84dd\u66e6\u81e3)||Birth name: Lan Huan ([[Chinese language|Chinese]]: \u84dd\u6da3).\nAlso known as ''Lord Zewu'' ([[Chinese language|Chinese]]: \u6cfd\u829c\u541b), or Brilliance Overgrowth Lord,<ref name=\"viki\" /> he is the leader and first young master of Lan sect, and one of the Twin Jades of Lan. He is known as one of the Three Zuns alongside his sworn brothers Jin Guangyao and Nie Mingjue. He wields the ''Shuoyue'' sword ([[Chinese language|Chinese]]: \u6714\u6708) and the ''Liebing'' flute ([[Chinese language|Chinese]]: \u88c2\u51b0). In contrast to his younger brother, he is a kind, gentle, and trusting person. \n|-\n| Huang Ziteng || Lan Qiren <br>([[Chinese language|Chinese]]: \u84dd\u542f\u4ec1)||The respected elder of Lan sect. The uncle of Lan Xichen and Lan Wangji. An extremely strict teacher who doesn't get along with Wei Wuxian.\n|-\n| Zheng Fanxing<ref>{{cite web|url=https://ent.china.com/movie/tv/11015529/20180524/32446333.html|title=\u300a\u9648\u60c5\u4ee4\u300b\u90d1\u7e41\u661f\u51fa\u6f14\u84dd\u601d\u8ffd \u98ce\u5ea6\u7fe9\u7fe9\u7684\u82f1\u4fca\u5c11\u5e74|date=May 24, 2018|website=China.com|language=zh|access-date=May 3, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190503144505/https://ent.china.com/movie/tv/11015529/20180524/32446333.html|archive-date=May 3, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><br> <small>Jiang Yiting (young)</small> || Lan Sizhui <br>([[Chinese language|Chinese]]: \u84dd\u601d\u8ffd)|| Birth name: Previously Wen Yuan ([[Chinese language|Chinese]]: \u6e29\u82d1), now Lan Yuan ([[Chinese language|Chinese]]: \u84dd\u613f).\nA disciple of Lan sect. He was found by Wei Wuxian among the remains of the Wen sect and was raised by him, and later brought back to the Lan sect by Lan Wangji. He is a calm and elegant individual who carries himself intelligently and sensibly, and is very mature for his age. As a child, he was more of a troublemaker. He is close friends with Lan Jingyi and Jin Ling.\n|-\n| Guo Cheng<ref>{{cite web|url=https://wemedia.ifeng.com/62114459/wemedia.shtml|title=\u300a\u9648\u60c5\u4ee4\u300b\u66dd\u89d2\u8272\u6d77\u62a5 \u90ed\u4e1e\u9970\u84dd\u666f\u4eea\u5f15\u671f\u5f85|date=May 25, 2018|website=ifeng|language=zh|access-date=May 3, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190503144502/https://wemedia.ifeng.com/62114459/wemedia.shtml|archive-date=May 3, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> || Lan Jingyi <br>([[Chinese language|Chinese]]: \u84dd\u666f\u4eea) || A disciple of Lan sect. Compared to the tranquil personalities of most of his fellow Lan sect members, he is short-tempered and impatient, but kind at heart, and known in the fanbase as the \"most un-Lan Lan to ever Lan in the history of Lan\". He is close friends with Lan Sizhui and Jin Ling.\n|-\n| [[Carman Lee]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ent.huanqiu.com/movie/yingshi-neidi/2018-06/12265555.html?agt=15422|title=\u300a\u9648\u60c5\u4ee4\u300b\u66dd\u5267\u7167 \u674e\u82e5\u5f64\u6f14\u7ece\u84dd\u5bb6\u5bb6\u4e3b|date=June 15, 2018|website=Huanqiu|language=zh}}</ref> || Lan Yi <br>([[Chinese language|Chinese]]: \u84dd\u7ffc)|| The only female head in the history of Lan sect. She invented the infamous Chord Assassination technique, and was responsible for guarding a piece of the ''Stygian Iron'' ([[Chinese language|Chinese]]: \u9634\u94c1).\n|}\n\n====Lanling Jin Sect==== \n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! style=\"width:13%\"|Actor !! style=\"width:17%\"|Character !! Introduction  \n|-\n| Shen Xiaohai || Jin Guangshan <br>([[Chinese language|Chinese]]: \u91d1\u5149\u5584)||The leader of Jin sect. The father of Jin Guangyao, Jin Zixuan and Mo Xuanyu. He is known as a womanizer and has many illegitimate children.\n|-\n| Hu Xiaoting || Madame Jin <br>([[Chinese language|Chinese]]: \u91d1\u592b\u4eba)|| The wife of Jin Guangshan and mother of Jin Zixuan.\n|-\n| Zhu Zanjin<ref>{{cite web|url=https://3g.163.com/ent/article/DHH2ASHI000380EN.html|title=\u6731\u8d5e\u9526\u300a\u9648\u60c5\u4ee4\u300b \u9ad8\u5ea6\u8fd8\u539f\"\u91d1\u5149\u7476\"\u5927\u83b7\u597d\u8bc4|date=May 11, 2018|website=Netease|language=zh|access-date=May 3, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190503144507/https://3g.163.com/ent/article/DHH2ASHI000380EN.html|archive-date=May 3, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> || Jin Guangyao <br>([[Chinese language|Chinese]]: \u91d1\u5149\u7476)|| Birth name: Meng Yao ([[Chinese language|Chinese]]: \u5b5f\u7476).\nAlso known as ''Lord Lianfang'' ([[Chinese language|Chinese]]: \u655b\u82b3\u5c0a), or Hidden Fragrance Master,<ref name=\"viki\" /> he is the illegitimate son of Jin Guangshan and became the leader of Jin sect after the latter's death. He is known as one of the Three Zuns alongside his sworn brothers Lan Xichen and Nie Mingjue. He wields the ''Hensheng'' ([[Chinese language|Chinese]]: \u6068\u751f [[pinyin]]: ''H\u00e8nsh\u0113ng'') sword. He worked as a servant of the Nie sect and as a spy in the Wen sect before winning his father's approval to join the Jin sect after the Sunshot Campaign. Due to his identity as a prostitute's son, he feels inferior and is determined to prove himself. He is known for wearing a mask of pleasantry and his smooth demeanor. He greatly admires Lan Xichen, who was the only person who showed him kindness during his days as a servant.\n|-\n| Cao Yuchen<ref name=su />  || Jin Zixuan <br>([[Chinese language|Chinese]]: \u91d1\u5b50\u8f69)|| The son of Jin Guangshan, Jin Ling's father and Jiang Yanli's husband. He is proud and vain, but also upright and just. He scorns Jiang Yanli at first but grows to care for her and eventually falls in love with her.\n|-\n| Yao Shuhao<ref name=su />  || Jin Zixun <br>([[Chinese language|Chinese]]: \u91d1\u5b50\u52cb)|| The cousin of Jin Zixuan. He is arrogant and conceited and holds immense dislike for Wei Wuxian.\n|- \n| Jin Luying || Qin Su <br>([[Chinese language|Chinese]]: \u79e6\u612b)|| The wife of Jin Guangyao, who she happens to be related to; the daughter of Qin Cangye, leader of the Laoling Qin sect, a subsidiary of Jin sect.\n|-\n| Qi Peixin<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ent.163.com/18/0524/21/DIJPAU6900038793.html|title=\u65b0\u664b\u5c0f\u9c9c\u8089\u6f06\u57f9\u946b\u6311\u6218\u300a\u9648\u60c5\u4ee4\u300b\u4eba\u6c14\u89d2\u8272\"\u5927\u5c0f\u59d0\"|date=May 24, 2018|website=Netease|language=zh|access-date=May 3, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190503144503/http://ent.163.com/18/0524/21/DIJPAU6900038793.html|archive-date=May 3, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> || Jin Ling <br>([[Chinese language|Chinese]]: \u91d1\u51cc)||[[Courtesy name]]: Rulan ([[Chinese language|Chinese]]: \u5982\u5170).\nThe sole heir of Jin sect, Wei Wuxian's nephew, and the orphaned son of Jin Zixuan and Jiang Yanli. He wields the ''Suihua'' ([[Chinese language|Chinese]]: \u5c81\u534e\u5c0a) sword and is also an excellent archer. He has a dog named Fairy who often torments Wei Wuxian as comic relief. He is prideful, somewhat immature, and short-tempered, but can also be kind and loyal if necessary. He is close friends with Lan Sizhui and Lan Jingyi.\n|-\n| Wang Yifei<ref>{{cite web|url=https://kknews.cc/zh-sg/entertainment/9oym59q.html|title=\u300a\u9648\u60c5\u4ee4\u300b\u70ed\u62cd\u4e2d \"\u7ef5\u7ef5\"\u738b\u827a\u970f\u9020\u578b\u9996\u66dd\u5149\u83b7\u4e66\u7c89\u9ad8\u5ea6\u8bc4\u4ef7|date=June 29, 2018|website=Kknews.cc|language=zh|access-date=May 3, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190503144504/https://kknews.cc/zh-sg/entertainment/9oym59q.html|archive-date=May 3, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> ||  Luo Qingyang <br>([[Chinese language|Chinese]]: \u7f57\u9752\u7f8a) || Also known as Mian Mian ([[Chinese language|Chinese]]: \u7ef5\u7ef5). A disciple of Jin sect. She is unafraid to speak up for what's right and later left Jin sect due to differing beliefs on Wei Wuxian, being one of the only characters aside from Lan Wangji who is willing to speak up for him.\n|- \n|}\n\n====Qinghe Nie Sect==== \n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! style=\"width:13%\"|Actor !! style=\"width:17%\"|Character !! Introduction  \n|-\n| Wang Yizhou<ref name=su>{{cite web|url=http://ent.ifeng.com/a/20180525/43052227_0.shtml|title=\u300a\u9648\u60c5\u4ee4\u300b\u66dd\u6d77\u62a5 \u65b0\u9c9c\u9762\u5b54\u6253\u9020\u9ad8\u989c\u503c\u53e4\u88c5\u4ed9\u4fa0\u5267|date=May 25, 2018|website=ifeng|language=zh|access-date=May 3, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190503144507/http://ent.ifeng.com/a/20180525/43052227_0.shtml|archive-date=May 3, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><br> <small>Xuan Yuewen (young)</small>   || Nie Mingjue <br>([[Chinese language|Chinese]]:  \u8042\u660e\u73a6)|| Also known as ''Lord Chifeng'' ([[Chinese language|Chinese]]: \u8d64\u950b\u5c0a), or the Scarlet Peak Master,<ref name=\"viki\" /> he is the leader of Nie sect. He is known as one of the Three Zuns alongside his sworn brothers Lan Xichen and Jin Guangyao. He wields the ''Baxia'' ([[Chinese language|Chinese]]: \u9738\u4e0b) saber. He is strict, just, and known for his intolerance toward evil. However, he has a terrible temper and holds extreme grudges towards Jin Guangyao.\n|-\n| Ji Li<ref name=su /><br> <small>Xu Weiluo(young)</small>  || Nie Huaisang <br>([[Chinese language|Chinese]]: \u8042\u6000\u6851)|| The leader of Nie sect after Nie Mingjue's death and younger half-brother of Nie Mingjue. He is well known for his incompetence and is nicknamed the Head-Shaker. Often, he is seen carrying around a fan. However, there is more to him than most think.\n|-\n|}\n\n====Qishan Wen Sect==== \n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! style=\"width:13%\"|Actor !! style=\"width:17%\"|Character !! Introduction  \n|-\n|Xiu Qing || Wen Ruohan <br>([[Chinese language|Chinese]]: \u6e29\u82e5\u5bd2)|| The leader of Wen sect, Chief Cultivator, and father of Wen Chao and Wen Xu. He is an ambitious man who wants to rule over the five sects by restoring the  ''Stygian Iron'' ([[Chinese language|Chinese]]: \u9634\u94c1).\n|-\n| Wang Rong || Wen Xu <br>([[Chinese language|Chinese]]: \u6e29\u65ed)|| The eldest son of Wen Ruohan, a cruel and violent man. He is less intelligent, but also less cowardly, than his brother. \n|-\n| He Peng<ref>{{cite web|url=https://ent.qq.com/a/20180831/058446.htm|title=\u300a\u9648\u60c5\u4ee4\u300b\u6740\u9752 \u8d3a\u9e4f\u9996\u6f14\u4ed9\u4fa0\u5267\u53d8\u5937\u9675\u8001\u7956\u5bf9\u5934|date=August 31, 2018|website=Tencent|language=zh|access-date=May 3, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190503144505/https://ent.qq.com/a/20180831/058446.htm|archive-date=May 3, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> || Wen Chao <br>([[Chinese language|Chinese]]: \u6e29\u6641)|| The second son of Wen Ruohan. He is one of the main antagonists in the first half of the show and is cruel, arrogant, and rude. However, in the face of danger, he immediately adopts a pathetic, cowardly nature due to his fright. He enjoys punishing and hurting others, furthering his sadistic nature.\n|-\n| [[Meng Ziyi]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ent.163.com/18/0426/15/DGB1B3Q0000380EN.html|title=\u300a\u9648\u60c5\u4ee4\u300b\u5f00\u673a \u5b5f\u5b50\u4e49\"\u6e29\u60c5\"\u6d77\u62a5\u589e\u6dfb\u795e\u79d8\u611f|date=April 26, 2018|website=Netease|language=zh|access-date=May 3, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190418140530/http://ent.163.com/18/0426/15/DGB1B3Q0000380EN.html|archive-date=April 18, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> || Wen Qing <br>([[Chinese language|Chinese]]:  \u6e29\u60c5)|| A renowned physician of the Wen sect and Wen Ning's older sister. She is aloof, cold, and extremely intelligent. She is protective toward her brother and initially dislikes Wei Wuxian, but eventually warms up to him as he becomes one of the only people to treat her kindly after the Wen sect is overthrown.\n|-\n| Yu Bin<ref>{{cite web|url=https://ent.qq.com/a/20180504/030050.htm|title=\u300a\u9648\u60c5\u4ee4\u300b\u5f00\u62cd \u4e8e\u658c\u51fa\u6f14\u6e29\u5b81\u9020\u578b\u8fd8\u539f\u83b7\u8d5e|date=May 4, 2018|website=Tencent|language=zh|access-date=May 3, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190503144507/https://ent.qq.com/a/20180504/030050.htm|archive-date=May 3, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> <br> <small>Su Qiuyi (young)</small>|| Wen Ning <br>([[Chinese language|Chinese]]: \u6e29\u5b81)||[[Courtesy name]]: Qionglin ([[Chinese language|Chinese]]: \u743c\u6797).\nAlso known as ''The Ghost General'' ([[Chinese language|Chinese]]: \u9b3c\u5c06\u519b), he is the right-hand man of Wei Wuxian during his time as the Yiling Patriarch. He was a shy person and a stutterer when he was alive due to his strange illness and grew to trust Wei Wuxian after being showered with kindness by him. As a fierce corpse, he is prone to outbursts of anger, but otherwise remains innocent, gentle, and shy.\n|-\n| Feng Mingjing || Wen Zhuliu <br>([[Chinese language|Chinese]]: \u6e29\u9010\u6d41)|| Also known as the ''Core-Melting Hand'' ([[Chinese language|Chinese]]: \u5316\u4e39\u624b) due to his ability to melt a Golden Core and is Wen Chao's protector. The Wen Sect's most powerful warrior, he holds to a strict and inscrutable code which included undying loyalty to his cruel masters.\n|-\n| Lu Enjie || Wang Lingjiao <br>([[Chinese language|Chinese]]: \u738b\u7075\u5a07)|| The former maid of Wen Chao's wife and Wen Chao's lover. She is an arrogant and pompous woman; however, upon facing any real threat, she immediately cowers, for unlike Wen Chao she is not only cowardly but also inept.\n|-\n| Zhang Bin || Wen Mao <br>([[Chinese language|Chinese]]: \u6e29\u536f)|| An ancestor of the Wen sect.\n|-\n|}\n\n====Yunmeng Jiang Sect====\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! style=\"width:13%\"|Actor !! style=\"width:17%\"|Character !! Introduction  \n|-\n|Lu Jianmin || Jiang Fengmian <br>([[Chinese language|Chinese]]: \u6c5f\u67ab\u7720) || The leader of Jiang sect, father of Jiang Yanli and Jiang Cheng. He is a kind and gentle man but holds favoritism towards Wei Wuxian.\n|-\n|Zhang Jingtong || Yu Ziyuan <br>([[Chinese language|Chinese]]: \u865e\u7d2b\u9e22) || Also known as Madame Yu or San Niang. Jiang Fengmian's wife, mother of Jiang Yanli and Jiang Cheng, and original owner of the ''Zidian'' ([[Chinese language|Chinese]]: \u7d2b\u7535) bracelet. She appears tough and strict but cares for her children and husband deep down, though she dislikes Wei Wuxian.\n|-\n| Wang Zhuocheng<ref>{{cite web|url=https://new.qq.com/omn/20180705/20180705A0OC7A.html|title=\u300a\u9648\u60c5\u4ee4\u300b\u66dd\u5149\u5267\u7167 \u6c6a\u5353\u6210\u88ab\u79f0\u4e3a\u65b0\u751f\u4ee3\"\u575e\"\u4e3b|date=July 5, 2018|website=Tencent|language=zh|access-date=May 3, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190503144459/https://new.qq.com/omn/20180705/20180705A0OC7A.html|archive-date=May 3, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><br> <small>Huang Zhenchen (young)</small> || Jiang Cheng <br>([[Chinese language|Chinese]]: \u6c5f\u6f84)||[[Courtesy name]]: Wanyin ([[Chinese language|Chinese]]: \u665a\u541f).\nAlso known as Sandu Shengshou ({{zh|c=\u4e09\u6bd2\u5723\u624b}}), or ''Three Poisons Sage'',<ref name=\"viki\" /> he is the leader of Jiang sect following Jiang Fengmian's death. He wields the ''Sandu'' ([[Chinese language|Chinese]]: \u4e09\u6bd2) sword and the ''Zidian'' ([[Chinese language|Chinese]]: \u7d2b\u7535) ring. He is a straight-laced and strict man who abides by the rules. He has a bad temper but deeply cares for his loved ones, especially his sister. He had a great relationship with Wei Wuxian, but their relationship deteriorated due to differing beliefs; however, they later made up at the end of the show. For some time, he had a crush on Wen Qing, until Wen Chao ordered the death of his parents, causing him to harbor hate for the Wen sect; however, he could not bring himself to hate her completely. He dotes on his nephew Jin Ling, though he is also strict and sharp-tongued toward him.\n|- \n| [[Lulu Xuan|Xuan Lu]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ent.163.com/18/0820/16/DPLSNJMT000380EO.html|title=\u5ba3\u7490\u300a\u9648\u60c5\u4ee4\u300b\u6740\u9752 \u642d\u6863\u8096\u6218\u6f14\u7ece\u59d0\u5f1f\u4eb2\u60c5\u5f15\u671f\u5f85|date=August 20, 2018|website=Netease|language=zh|access-date=May 3, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190503144506/http://ent.163.com/18/0820/16/DPLSNJMT000380EO.html|archive-date=May 3, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> <br> <small>Ye Xuantong (young)</small>|| Jiang Yanli <br>([[Chinese language|Chinese]]: \u6c5f\u538c\u79bb) || Jiang Cheng's older sister, Wei Wuxian's disciple elder sister, Jin Zixuan's wife and Jin Ling's mother. She is a kind, understanding, and caring person who protects her brothers and provides emotional support. She also appears to be a very good cook, with her best dish being a lotus root and pork rib soup that she often makes for her brothers. Though she is very kind, she appears to have somewhat delicate feelings, as shown when she is snubbed multiple times by Jin Zixuan.\n|-\n|}\n\n====Yi City Arc==== \n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! style=\"width:13%\"|Actor !! style=\"width:17%\"|Character !! Introduction  \n|-\n| Song Jiyang<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ent.ifeng.com/a/20180518/43050508_0.shtml|title=\u5b8b\u7ee7\u626c\u53c2\u6f14\u300a\u9648\u60c5\u4ee4\u300b\u4fca\u6717\u5916\u8868\u5f15\u671f\u5f85|date=May 18, 2018|website=ifeng|language=zh|access-date=May 3, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190503144503/http://ent.ifeng.com/a/20180518/43050508_0.shtml|archive-date=May 3, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> || Xiao Xingchen <br>([[Chinese language|Chinese]]: \u6653\u661f\u5c18)|| Also known as ''Daozhang'' ([[Chinese language|Chinese]]: \u9053\u957f), he is one of Baoshan Sanren's students who left the mountain for the mortal world. He wields the ''Shuanghua'' ([[Chinese language|Chinese]]: \u971c\u534e) sword and was best friends with Song Lan. He is gentle on the outside but determined on the inside. \n|-\n| Li Bowen<ref>{{cite web|url=http://wemedia.ifeng.com/68994882/wemedia.shtml|title=\u674e\u6cca\u6587\u51fa\u6f14\u300a\u9648\u60c5\u4ee4\u300b \u53e4\u88c5\u9020\u578b\u795e\u8fd8\u539f\u5b8b\u5b50\u741b|date=July 13, 2018|website=ifeng|language=zh|access-date=May 3, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190503144506/http://wemedia.ifeng.com/68994882/wemedia.shtml|archive-date=May 3, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> || Song Lan <br>([[Chinese language|Chinese]]:  \u5b8b\u5c9a)|| [[Courtesy name]]: Song Zichen ([[Chinese language|Chinese]]: \u5b8b\u5b50\u741b).\nA cultivator from Baixue Temple, and best friend of Xiao Xingchen. He wields the ''Fuxue'' ([[Chinese language|Chinese]]: \u62c2\u96ea) sword.\n|-\n| Wang Haoxuan<ref>{{cite web|url=https://wallstreetcn.com/articles/3394383|title=\u4ece\u300a\u6c99\u6d77\u300b\u7684\u8f6f\u840c\u5c11\u5e74\u5230\u300a\u9648\u60c5\u4ee4\u300b\u7684\u8179\u9ed1\u53cd\u6d3e\uff0c95\u540e\u65b0\u751f\u4ee3\u738b\u7693\u8f69\u672a\u6765\u53ef\u671f|date=August 24, 2018|website=Wall Street|language=zh|access-date=May 3, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190503144505/https://wallstreetcn.com/articles/3394383|archive-date=May 3, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> || Xue Yang <br>([[Chinese language|Chinese]]:  \u859b\u6d0b)||[[Courtesy name]]: Chengmei ([[Chinese language|Chinese]]: \u6210\u7f8e).\nA guest disciple of the Wen sect who has an affiliation with the ''Stygian Iron'' ([[Chinese language|Chinese]]: \u9634\u94c1). He wields the ''Jiangzai'' ([[Chinese language|Chinese]]: \u964d\u707e) sword. He is known for his evil and twisted ways.\n|-\n| Chen Zhuoxuan<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sohu.com/a/238446430_100116398|title=\u9648\u5353\u7487\u51fa\u6f14\u300a\u9648\u60c5\u4ee4\u300b\u963f\u83c1|date=June 29, 2018|website=Sohu|language=zh|access-date=May 3, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190503144507/http://www.sohu.com/a/238446430_100116398|archive-date=May 3, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> || Ah Qing <br>([[Chinese language|Chinese]]: \u963f\u7b90)|| A young maiden who lived on the streets and an expert at pretending to be blind. She followed Xiao Xingchen after meeting him.\n|-\n|}\n\n====Others==== \n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! style=\"width:13%\"|Actor !! style=\"width:17%\"|Character !! Introduction  \n|-\n| Feng Cong<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sohu.com/a/249434938_486930|title=\u300a\u9648\u60c5\u4ee4\u300b \u51af\u806a\uff1a\u6f14\u53cd\u6d3e\uff0c\u6ca1\u6709\u4eba\u9a82\u624d\u662f\u5931\u8d25\u4e86|date=August 22, 2018|website=Sohu|language=zh|access-date=May 3, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190503144459/http://www.sohu.com/a/249434938_486930|archive-date=May 3, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> || Su She <br>([[Chinese language|Chinese]]: \u82cf\u6d89)||[[Courtesy name]]: Minshan ([[Chinese language|Chinese]]: \u60af\u5584).\nThe wimp leader of the Moling Su sect. A former outer disciple of the Lan Sect, whom he betrayed and left to establish his own with the support of Jin Guangyao, whom he holds great respect for. He is jealous of Lan Wangji's talents and has always imitated his actions.\n|- \n|Liu Tingyu || Baoshan Sanren <br>([[Chinese language|Chinese]]: \u62b1\u5c71\u6563\u4eba)|| The teacher of Xiao Xingchen and Cangse Sanren, Wei Wuxian's mother.\n|-\n| Cao Junxiang<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sohu.com/a/284078202_161623|title=\u300a\u9648\u60c5\u4ee4\u300b\u5c06\u64ad \u66f9\u5cfb\u7965\u53d8\u8eab\u4e8c\u6b21\u5143\u7f8e\u5c11\u5e74|date=December 24, 2018|website=Sohu|language=zh|access-date=May 3, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190503144503/http://www.sohu.com/a/284078202_161623|archive-date=May 3, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> || Ouyang Zizhen <br>([[Chinese language|Chinese]]: \u6b27\u9633\u5b50\u771f)|| The single child of the Baling Ouyang sect's leader.\n|- \n|Yu Zikuang || Xue Chonghai <br>([[Chinese language|Chinese]]: \u859b\u91cd\u4ea5)|| The ancient owner of the ''Stygian Iron'' ([[Chinese language|Chinese]]: \u9634\u94c1).\n|-\n|}\n\n{{Hidden begin|title=Extended cast|titlestyle=background:#D8D8D8}} \n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! style=\"width:13%\"|Actor !! style=\"width:17%\"|Character !! Introduction  \n|-\n| Liu Yinjun || Jin Chan <br>([[Chinese language|Chinese]]: \u91d1\u9610) || A disciple of Jin sect. He bullied Jin Ling, but is stopped by Wei Wuxian.  \n|- \n|Lin Chenyue || Sixth disciple <br> ([[Chinese language|Chinese]]: \u516d\u5e08\u5f1f) || Disciple of Jiang sect. \n|- \n|Jiang Weijia || Chief of Nie <br> ([[Chinese language|Chinese]]: