n sect.\n|-\n|Jiao Changshun || Song Lan's teacher <br>([[Chinese language|Chinese]]: \u5b8b\u5c9a\u5e08\u5085)|| \n|-\n|Shen Xin || Funeral Shopkeeper <br>([[Chinese language|Chinese]]: \u4e27\u846c\u8001\u592a)|| \n|-\n|Huang Ying || Granny Liu <br>([[Chinese language|Chinese]]: \u5218\u5a46\u5a46)|| \n|-\n|Liu Fengmin<ref name=two>{{cite web|url=http://dy.163.com/v2/article/detail/EMPHPBL005370H44.html|title=\u300a\u9648\u60c5\u4ee4\u300b\u8fd8\u6709\u9690\u85cf\u5267\u60c5\uff0c\u8042\u6000\u6851\u6e29\u6641\u90fd\u66fe\u626e\u6210\u8001\u5934\uff1f\u6697\u4e2d\u8fd0\u7b79\u5e37\u5e44|website=Netease|language=zh|access-date=2019-10-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191011230904/http://dy.163.com/v2/article/detail/EMPHPBL005370H44.html|archive-date=2019-10-11|url-status=live}}</ref> || Lao Zhang (Wen Chao) <br>([[Chinese language|Chinese]]: \u8001\u4e08\uff08\u6e29\u6641\uff09)|| \n|-\n|Sun Liang<ref name=two />|| Lao Zhang (Nie Huaisang)<br>([[Chinese language|Chinese]]: \u8001\u4e08\uff08\u8042\u6000\u6851\uff09)|| \n|-\n|}\n{{Hidden end}}\n\n==Production==\n===Pre-production and filming=== \n[[File:Hengdian World Studios 001.jpg|thumb|250px|[[Hengdian World Studios]], the main filming site of the series]]\nPre-production of the drama took two and a half years; including writing and modifying of the script, establishing the world view structure and art concept, as well as building of sets.<ref name=zhuan>{{cite web|url=http://ent.people.com.cn/n1/2019/0705/c1012-31216912.html|title=\u4e13\u8bbf\u300a\u9648\u60c5\u4ee4\u300b\u603b\u5236\u7247\u4eba\uff1a\u5e74\u8f7b\u89c2\u4f17\u5bf9\u5267\u7684\u5ba1\u7f8e\u66f4\u52a0\u7406\u6027|date=July 5, 2019|website=People's Daily|language=zh|access-date=July 8, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190705114444/http://ent.people.com.cn/n1/2019/0705/c1012-31216912.html|archive-date=July 5, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> The project was first announced in March 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ent.sina.com.cn/v/m/2018-03-13/doc-ifyscsmv0829869.shtml|title=\u77e5\u540d\u803d\u7f8e\u5c0f\u8bf4\u300a\u9b54\u9053\u7956\u5e08\u300b\u5c06\u62cd\u5267 \u5b9a\u540d\u300a\u9648\u60c5\u4ee4\u300b|date=March 13, 2018|website=Sina|language=zh|access-date=May 3, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190503144505/http://ent.sina.com.cn/v/m/2018-03-13/doc-ifyscsmv0829869.shtml|archive-date=May 3, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nThe series is co-directed by Zheng Weiwen and Chen Jialin; and the script written by a team consisting of Yang Xia, Deng Yaoyu, Ma Jing and Guo Guangyun. The main producers are credited to be Fang Feng, Yang Xia, Wang Chu and Liu Mingyi; while Yang Xia and Ji Peng serve as the art directors.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://cj.sina.com.cn/articles/view/5159017394/133805bb201900kgok|title=120\u5f20\u6982\u5ff5\u56fe\u3001300\u4eba\u7f8e\u672f\u56e2\u961f\uff0c\u300a\u9648\u60c5\u4ee4\u300b\"\u660e\u77e5\u4e0d\u53ef\u4e3a\u800c\u4e3a\u4e4b\"|date=July 7, 2019|website=Sina|language=zh|access-date=July 9, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190709160214/https://cj.sina.com.cn/articles/view/5159017394/133805bb201900kgok|archive-date=July 9, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> The drama was filmed from April 2018 to August 2018 at [[Hengdian World Studios]] and [[Guizhou]].<ref name=kai>{{cite web|url=http://ent.163.com/18/0426/13/DGARNE8U00038793.html|title=\u7535\u89c6\u5267\u300a\u9648\u60c5\u4ee4\u300b\u5f00\u62cd \u8096\u6218\u738b\u4e00\u535a\u9886\u8854\u9ad8\u989c\u503c\u9635\u5bb9|date=April 26, 2018|website=Netease|language=zh|access-date=May 3, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190503144504/http://ent.163.com/18/0426/13/DGARNE8U00038793.html|archive-date=May 3, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> <ref>{{cite web|url=https://ent.china.com/movie/tv/11015529/20180824/33677517.html|title=\u738b\u4e00\u535a\u300a\u9648\u60c5\u4ee4\u300b\u6740\u9752 \u611f\u6069\u5267\u7ec4\u4e0d\u820d\u79bb\u522b|date=August 24, 2018|website=China.com|language=zh|access-date=May 3, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190503144505/https://ent.china.com/movie/tv/11015529/20180824/33677517.html|archive-date=May 3, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> Two weeks before filming, the cast gathered for script reading sessions and underwent martial arts and etiquette training.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://k.sina.com.cn/article_5737990122_15602c7ea01900h4wh.html?from=ent&subch=oent|title=\u62cd\u620f \u300a\u9648\u60c5\u4ee4\u300b\u768420\u4ef6\u4e8b|date=July 17, 2019|website=Sina|language=zh}}</ref> \n\nDue to the censorship in China, all [[yaoi|BL]] content is removed from the drama and changes are made to the overall plot.<ref name=xian>{{cite web|url=http://www.xinhuanet.com/ent/2018-08/21/c_1123302974.htm|title=\u5bfc\u6f14\u90d1\u4f1f\u6587\u6267\u5bfc\u300a\u9648\u60c5\u4ee4\u300b\u7eed\u5199\u4ed9\u4fa0\u7f18|date=August 21, 2018|website=Xinhua News Agency|language=zh|access-date=May 3, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190503144504/http://www.xinhuanet.com/ent/2018-08/21/c_1123302974.htm|archive-date=May 3, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> As the original novel was written in a \"flashback\" style, additional scenes had to be inserted to improve the flow of the story.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bjnews.com.cn/ent/2019/07/11/602345.html|title=\u300a\u9648\u60c5\u4ee4\u300b\u738b\u4e00\u535a\u3001\u8096\u6218\u6f14\u201c\u5fd8\u7fa1\u201d\u538b\u529b\u591a\u8fc7\u5174\u594b|date=July 11, 2019|website=Beijing News|language=zh|access-date=November 10, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190925030501/http://www.bjnews.com.cn/ent/2019/07/11/602345.html|archive-date=September 25, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> \nTwo versions of the script were prepared; one is told in the chronological order of story development, and the other is a narrative trajectory that follows the original novel. Finally, on the basis of not breaking the core of the original story, and to fully develop and layer the storyline, the team decided to adopt a mixture of both styles.<ref name=zhuan /> To better fuse the different storylines together, the team decided to forgo traditional styles of filming, and more suspense was used in the lens composition settings.<ref name=xian /> \n\nDespite being termed as \"xianxia\" drama, ''The Untamed'' includes many elements of traditional [[wuxia]] dramas, fused with a new style.<ref name=\"thepaper\">{{cite web|url=https://www.thepaper.cn/newsDetail_forward_3868021|title=\u300a\u9648\u60c5\u4ee4\u300b\uff1a\u65b0\u6b66\u4fa0\"\u5f52\u6765\"|date=July 4, 2019|website=The Paper|language=zh|access-date=July 9, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190709160841/https://www.thepaper.cn/newsDetail_forward_3868021|archive-date=July 9, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> Using traditional wuxia values such as \"chivalry and courage\", it allows the younger audience to better relate to the drama.<ref name=\"thepaper\" />\n\n===Casting=== \nThe casting director gave a special \"character card\" to each of the cast members; which includes detailed descriptions of the character such as the looks, height, clothing style and even specific details such as \"Wei Wuxian has a natural smiling face\".<ref name=zhuan /> \n\n[[Xiao Zhan]] and [[Wang Yibo]] were announced as the lead actors in April 2018.<ref name=kai /> Xiao was recommended by a friend of the producer Yang Xia, who chose him because of his \"clean gaze\". Wang got the role through an audition, because of his \"natural coldness\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://new.qq.com/omn/20190723/20190723A0RYJ300.html|title=\u300a\u9648\u60c5\u4ee4\u300b\u66dd\u9009\u89d2\u5185\u5e55\uff1a\u8096\u6218\u51ed\u53e4\u88c5\u7167\u5165\u9009\uff0c\u738b\u4e00\u535a\u7b2c\u4e00\u8f6e\u88ab\u6dd8\u6c70|date=July 23, 2019|website=Tencent|language=zh|access-date=August 16, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190816192053/https://new.qq.com/omn/20190723/20190723A0RYJ300.html|archive-date=August 16, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nLu Zhixing and Bian Jiang, who dubbed Wei Wuxian and Lan Wangji in the audio drama and [[Mo Dao Zu Shi|donghua]] adaptation of ''Mo Dao Zu Shi'' respectively, were hired to voice Wei Wuxian and Lan Wangji in the series.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://new.qq.com/omn/20190713/20190713A04LB700.html|title=\u4ece\u65e0\u540d\u201c\u66ff\u58f0\u201d\u5230\u767b\u4e0a\u300a\u9648\u60c5\u4ee4\u300b\u6d77\u62a5\uff0c\u914d\u97f3\u6f14\u5458\u51fa\u5708\u7b80\u53f2|date=July 13, 2019|website=Tencent|language=zh|access-date=November 10, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191110071029/https://new.qq.com/omn/20190713/20190713A04LB700.html|archive-date=November 10, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> \n\n===Design and concept===\nAccording to producer Yang Xia, while designing the sets and costumes of the different sects, the team started out by searching for a culture placement where the design could be based on.<ref name=zhuan /> The costume designer of the drama is Chen Tongxun.<ref name=design1 /> \n\nFor the Gusu Lan sect, influence from the [[Song Dynasty]] were taken into consideration while designing the costumes and sets. While designing the \"jingshi\", blue and green shades were used to showcase the elegance and dignified strength/character of the sect; while darker shades of wood were used to show off the magnificence. Cascading collars and sleeves were used to design the clothes, to highlight the strictness of the sect.<ref name=zhuan /> \n\nFor the Yunmeng Jiang sect, influences from the [[Hubei]] and [[Jianghan district]] were taken. Warm and light colors were used to showcase the cheerful and free-spirited nature of the sect. The architecture and sets were designed to be widely spaced, and yarn was used to create the feeling of \"transparency\". Narrow sleeves and neat designs were used to highlight the \"wandering pugilistic\" feel of the sect. A water recycling device was used in the lotus lake of the set, allowing ripples to be seen on the lake surface. A special ceiling was built for the ancestral hall.<ref name=zhuan /> \n\nFor the Qinghe Nie sect, the set was designed to be surrounded by high walls and the entrance isn't easily seen because it was often invaded by Qishan Wen sect. For Qishan Wen sect, designs from the [[Shang dynasty]] were used. For Lanling Jin sect, the designs were inspired by the luxurious and elegance of the [[Tang dynasty]].<ref name=design>{{cite web|url=http://media.people.com.cn/n1/2019/0708/c14677-31219013.html|title=\u300a\u9648\u60c5\u4ee4\u300b\u91cc\u9970\u9b4f\u65e0\u7fa1\u5708\u7c89\u65e0\u6570 \u8096\u6218\u81ea\u79f0\u4e0e\u89d2\u8272\u4e0d\u4e00\u6837|date=July 8, 2019|website=People's Daily|language=zh|access-date=November 10, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190708025540/http://media.people.com.cn/n1/2019/0708/c14677-31219013.html|archive-date=July 8, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n===Controversies===\nA fire broke out at on July 11, 2018 while the cast and crew were filming in Nanma, [[Dongyang]], at a facility that belongs to Hengdian World Studios. The fire reportedly spread as wide as 300 square meters, and resulted in the death of two crew members.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ent.163.com/18/0713/09/DMJ8KJHT00038FO9.html|title=\u300a\u9648\u60c5\u4ee4\u300b\u5267\u7ec4\u6444\u5f71\u68da\u53d1\u751f\u706b\u707e \u73b0\u573a2\u4eba\u6b7b\u4ea1|date=July 13, 2018|website=Netease|language=zh|access-date=May 3, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190503144503/http://ent.163.com/18/0713/09/DMJ8KJHT00038FO9.html|archive-date=May 3, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nDuring filming, a rumor surfaced that the producers of the drama had replaced Lan Wangji as Wei Wuxian's love interest with a female character, Wen Qing. This rumor caused significant backlash amongst fans of the original novel.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ent.sina.com.cn/zl/bagua/2018-07-23/doc-ihftenhy8491682.shtml|title=\u5f3a\u62c6cp\u7684\u9648\u60c5\u4ee4\u7ec8\u4e8e\u906d\u5230\u4e86\u7c89\u4e1d\u7684\u5b7d\u529b\u56de\u9988|date=July 23, 2018|website=Sina|language=zh|access-date=May 3, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181011172949/http://ent.sina.com.cn/zl/bagua/2018-07-23/doc-ihftenhy8491682.shtml|archive-date=October 11, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> The production team strongly denied such claims.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ent.163.com/18/0719/09/DN2MATON00038FO9.html|title=\u300a\u9648\u60c5\u4ee4\u300b\u5267\u65b9\u56de\u5e94\u6f14\u5458\u5e26\u8d44\u8fdb\u7ec4\u4f20\u8a00\uff1a\u5747\u4e0d\u5c5e\u5b9e|date=July 19, 2018|website=Netease|language=zh|access-date=May 3, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190503144500/http://ent.163.com/18/0719/09/DN2MATON00038FO9.html|archive-date=May 3, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn July 29, 2019, Tencent announced that VIP users have the option to pay in order to watch episodes that have not yet aired. Starting from August 7, the final episode will be released early for some viewers who choose to avail the option. This has caused outrage among viewers of the show, who were concerned that this would open up the risk of the ending being spoiled and also the possibility that the episodes will be pirated, which will then have a negative effect on views. In response, Tencent explained that in this way, they can cater to demands of certain viewers who are requesting for episodes to be released faster while the rest can still watch the series at their preferred pace.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://tech.sina.com.cn/i/2019-08-01/doc-ihytcerm7837398.shtml|title=\u817e\u8baf\u89c6\u9891\u300a\u9648\u60c5\u4ee4\u300b\u8d85\u524d\u70b9\u64ad:\u8c01\u5265\u593a\u4e86VIP\u7684\u8ffd\u5267\u5feb\u4e50|date=August 1, 2019|website=Sina|language=zh|access-date=August 8, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190801103004/https://tech.sina.com.cn/i/2019-08-01/doc-ihytcerm7837398.shtml|archive-date=August 1, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==Soundtrack==\nThe main composer of the soundtrack is Lin Hai.<ref name=design1>{{cite web|url=https://ent.sina.com.cn/v/m/2019-07-04/doc-ihytcerm1217001.shtml|title=\u300a\u9648\u60c5\u4ee4\u300b\u5f00\u64ad\u5f15\u70ed\u8bae \u521b\u4f5c\u56e2\u961f\u5766\u8bda\u4e0d\u8db3\u63a5\u53d7\u6307\u6b63|date=July 4, 2019|website=Sina|language=zh|access-date=July 9, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190709154334/https://ent.sina.com.cn/v/m/2019-07-04/doc-ihytcerm1217001.shtml|archive-date=July 9, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> The theme song was titled \"\u5fd8\u7fa1\" ({{zh|c=|s=|t=|p=W\u00e0ngxi\u00e0n|l=}}) before being renamed from Episode 11 onwards to \"\u65e0\u7f81 ({{zh|c=|s=|t=|p=W\u00fa j\u012b;|l=}})\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ent.people.com.cn/n1/2019/0708/c1012-31221131.html|title=\u300a\u9648\u60c5\u4ee4\u300b\u56fd\u98ce\u97f3\u4e50\u4e13\u8f91\u91cd\u78c5\u4e0a\u7ebf \u8096\u6218\u738b\u4e00\u535a\"\u58f0\u52a8\"\u8be0\u91ca\u89d2\u8272\u5185\u5fc3|date=July 8, 2019|website=People.com|language=zh|access-date=July 8, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190708103556/http://ent.people.com.cn/n1/2019/0708/c1012-31221131.html|archive-date=July 8, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> On July 8, 2019, the digital album was released on [[QQ Music]] along with full version of the song as well as other character songs.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://y.qq.com/n/yqq/album/002Tryw33HIGNP.html?g_f=yqqjiaodian|title=\u9648\u60c5\u4ee4 \u56fd\u98ce\u97f3\u4e50\u4e13\u8f91\uff01|website=Tencent Music|access-date=2019-07-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190708042931/https://y.qq.com/n/yqq/album/002Tryw33HIGNP.html%3Fg_f%3Dyqqjiaodian|archive-date=2019-07-08|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://ent.huanqiu.com/movie/yingshi-neidi/2019-07/15179929.html?agt=15422|script-title=zh:\u300a\u9648\u60c5\u4ee4\u300b\u4eba\u7269\u66f2\u4e0a\u7ebf \u56fd\u97f5\u7f8e\u5b66\u6253\u5f00\u5185\u5fc3\u4e16\u754c|date=July 22, 2019|website=Huanqiu|language=zh}}</ref> The instrumental album was released on [[QQ Music]] on August 5, 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://music.douban.com/subject/34785471/|title=\u9648\u60c5\u4ee4 \u539f\u58f0\u97f3\u4e50\u4e13\u8f91|date=|website=Douban|language=zh|access-date=2019-11-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191110055226/https://music.douban.com/subject/34785471/|archive-date=2019-11-10|url-status=live}}</ref> \n\nThe physical album was released on November 2, 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://music.douban.com/subject/34878549/|title=\u9648\u60c5\u4ee4\u56fd\u98ce\u97f3\u4e50\u5927\u789f|date=|website=Douban|language=zh|access-date=2019-11-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191110055225/https://music.douban.com/subject/34878549/|archive-date=2019-11-10|url-status=live}}</ref> \n\n{{Infobox album\n| name       = ''The Untamed'' OST (\u9648\u60c5\u4ee4\u56fd\u98ce\u97f3\u4e50\u4e13\u8f91) \n| type       = Soundtrack\n| artist     = Various artists\n| cover      =\n| released   = {{start date|2019|07|08}}\n| recorded   = 2018\u20132019\n| genre      = [[Soundtrack]]\n| length     = \n| language   = {{hlist|[[Chinese language|Chinese]]}}\n| label      = {{hlist|New Style Media|[[QQ Music]]}}\n| producer   = Lin Hai\n}}\n{{Tracklist\n| collapsed       = \n| total_length    = \n| all_writing     = \n| all_lyrics      = \n| all_music       = \n| arranger_credits= \n| extra_column = Singers\n\n| title1          = Unrestrained (\u65e0\u7f81)\n| note1           = Theme song \u2013 duet version\n| lyrics1         = Cheng Yi, Ming Feng\n| music1          = Lin Hai\n| arranger1       =  \n| extra1          =  [[Xiao Zhan]] & [[Wang Yibo]] \n| length1         = 04:13\n\n| title2          =  Unrestrained (\u65e0\u7f81)\n| note2           = Theme song \u2013 special version\n| lyrics2        =  Cheng Yi, Ming Feng\n| music2         =  Lin Hai \n| arranger2      =  \n| extra2        = [[Bibi Zhou]] \n| length2       =04:14\n\n| title3          = Unrestrained (\u65e0\u7f81)\n| note3           = Theme song \u2013 solo version\n| lyrics3      