pi Palace]].<hr>In order for Andy to capture the full beauty of the [[Hagia Sophia]] in his drawings, he must learn to look at it in different ways.\n| LineColor = 3198FF\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = 19\n| Title = C'est Cheese\"<hr>\"C'est la Vie a Paris\n| WrittenBy = Rachel Lipman<hr>Mark Haslett\n| Aux2 = Dan Becker & Eric David Haddad<hr>Tom Smith & Jackie Bae\n| Aux3 = [[Paris]], [[France]]\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2019|08|12}}\n| ShortSummary = Leo needs to make his best dish for his French cooking class but can't think of the perfect thing to make.<hr> Mister Hockbar is overworking himself and everyone else at the Circo, so the kids and Luna try to find something in Paris to help him relax.\n| LineColor = 3198FF\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = 20\n| Title = D'Orsay Day\"<hr>\"Honey in Paris\n| WrittenBy = Joe Murray<hr> Peter Hannan\n| Aux2 = Dan Becker & Eric David Haddad<hr>Tom Smith & Jackie Bae\n| Aux3 = [[Paris]], [[France]]\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2019|08|13}}\n| ShortSummary = Andy is trying to make a perfect painting of his model train, but can't make it look 'alive' enough, so Luna takes him to [[Mus\u00e9e d'Orsay]] to show him other ways to paint.<hr>Honey escapes from her cage again and returns head over heels in love with someone named \"Mon Amour\". Carmen and her friends are determined to find out who exactly this mysterious stranger is.\n| LineColor = 3198FF\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = 21\n| Title = Lost and Found\"<hr>\"Time of Goodbye\n| WrittenBy = Joe Murray<hr>Rachel Lipman\n| Aux2 = Dan Becker & Eric David Haddad<hr>Tom Smith & Jackie Bae\n| Aux3 = [[Barcelona]], [[Spain]]\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2019|09|24}}<br>{{Start date|2020|2|5}} (USA)\n| ShortSummary = Se\u00f1or Fabuloso has lost his creativity and the kids and Luna travel across Barcelona to see if they can reignite his playful spirit, with the help of [[Antoni Gaud\u00ed]]'s unique architecture.<hr>It's [[Saint George's Day]] in Barcelona and Se\u00f1or Fabuloso is furious because it reminds him of losing track of his friend, making Carmen feel nervous about giving her newest friend Silvia a gift for the same reason.\n| LineColor = 3198FF\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = 22\n| Title = Castells in the Air\"<hr>\"Barcelona Birdy\n| WrittenBy = Peter Hannan<hr>Mark Haslett\n| Aux2 = Dan Becker & Eric David Haddad<hr>Tom Smith & Keith Silva\n| Aux3 = [[Barcelona]], [[Spain]]\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2019|09|25}} (Canada)<br>{{Start date|2020|05|19}} (USA)\n| ShortSummary = Carmen needs to help her new friend Ramona win the [[Castell]] contest in Barcelona, but Carmen's independent nature makes this harder than she thought.<hr>Leo helps a small bird named Eva get back to her nest. But it's at the very, very, very top of [[Montserrat (mountain)|Montserrat]]. Can he be brave enough to do it?\n| LineColor = 3198FF\n}}\n{{Episode List\n| EpisodeNumber = 23\n| Title = Stairway to Art Day\"<hr>\"Melvini Madness\n| WrittenBy = Peter Hannan<hr>Rachel Lipman\n| Aux2 = Dan Becker & Eric David Haddad<hr>Tom Smith & Keith Silva\n| Aux3 = [[Rio de Janeiro]], [[Brazil]]\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2019|09|26}} (Knowledge Kids)<br>{{Start date|2019|11|4}} (USA)<br>{{Start date|2020|01|18}} (Canada)\n| ShortSummary = Andy's Art Day Extravaganza is put on hold when his father needs him to go into the city to get a nail to fix the steps outside their trailer.<hr>Carmen accidentally wakes Pablo the Armadillo's Melvinis after he has left on vacation, and she needs to find a way to get them back to sleep again.\n| LineColor = 3198FF\n}}\n{{Episode List\n| EpisodeNumber = 24\n| Title = Andy's Big Show\"<hr>\"Leo Moves It\n| WrittenBy = Mark Haslett<hr>Joe Murray\n| Aux2 =  Tom Smith & Eric David Haddad<hr>Tom Smith & Keith Silva\n| Aux3 = [[Rio de Janeiro]], [[Brazil]]\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2019|09|27}}<br>{{Start date|2019|11|5}} (USA)<br>{{Start date|2020|01|19}} (Canada)\n|